docs.abstract: The company reported a net income of $2.9 billion in the third quarter, partly by being more efficient in its warehouses and data centers.
docs.snippet: The company reported a net income of $2.9 billion in the third quarter, partly by being more efficient in its warehouses and data centers.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon’s profits were hit or miss for its first couple of decades. But now, for the first time, they are starting to look consistent — with four consecutive quarters above $1 billion in profit.

headline.main: Amazon Squeezes Out More Profit as Sales Growth Slows
headline.print_headline: Sales Slow, But Amazon Clears Profit Of $1 Billion

docs.abstract: It was a technological wonder — until the retail landscape changed and new innovation, and greedy owners, arrived.
docs.snippet: It was a technological wonder — until the retail landscape changed and new innovation, and greedy owners, arrived.
docs.lead_paragraph: The orders poured in from everywhere — 105,000 a day at one point — so much so that the company became an economic force. It could make or break suppliers by promoting their products. It could dictate terms on manufacturing. Its headquarters city boomed as this tech-driven retailer built huge warehouses and factories and attracted other businesses and rivals. State and local governments complained that the company was harming small-town retailers.

headline.main: How Sears Was the Amazon of Its Day
headline.print_headline: How Sears Was the Amazon of Its Day

docs.abstract: The second series of the spy drama has gone down better in Germany than the first.
docs.snippet: The second series of the spy drama has gone down better in Germany than the first.
docs.lead_paragraph: BERLIN — When the spy series “Deutschland 83” had its premiere in 2015, it was portrayed as a breakthrough moment for German television. At that point, the country had yet to produce any prestige shows with an international following, unlike France and Denmark. The series, which followed a young East German soldier corralled into working as an undercover agent on the other side of the Iron Curtain, was the first German show to air on an American network, SundanceTV. In Britain it became the most-watched foreign-language drama ever.

headline.main: ‘Deutschland 83’ Was a Hit Abroad but a Flop at Home. What About ‘Deutschland 86’?

docs.abstract: Financial engineers like Eddie Lampert are wreaking havoc on American companies.
docs.snippet: Financial engineers like Eddie Lampert are wreaking havoc on American companies.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Sears, once America’s largest retailer, made its bankruptcy filing Monday in a White Plains courthouse, the proximate cause was the decision by Eddie Lampert, by far its biggest individual creditor and shareholder, not to make a $134 million loan payment that was due. “This is not so much a melting ice cube, but a puddle,” a lawyer for a large creditor told the federal Bankruptcy Court.

headline.main: The Billionaire Who Led Sears Into Bankruptcy Court

docs.abstract: The Emmy-winning TV creator talks about his return to television with “The Romanoffs” and addresses a harassment allegation.
docs.snippet: The Emmy-winning TV creator talks about his return to television with “The Romanoffs” and addresses a harassment allegation.
docs.lead_paragraph: Los Angeles — Before writing an episode of his new Amazon series “The Romanoffs,” Matthew Weiner would ring a small bell. The trinket was a Christmas gift from one of the writers on the show, and the sound it made was essential for “clearing the air,” Mr. Weiner said. “It was a moment of faith in intuition and the process.”

headline.main: Matthew Weiner on Life After ‘Mad Men,’ Sexual Harassment and His New Amazon Show
headline.print_headline: After ‘Mad Men,’ an Idea That Spans the Globe
